                        <country key="place_1000080">Italian</country>, <settlement key="place_7004264">Ferrara</settlement>
                        <!--ORIGINAL: Italian, Ferrara-->
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate calendar="Gregorian" cert="high" when="1467">1467 (or slightly earlier)</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Identifiable as the MS. illuminated for <persName key="person_1155" role="fmo"><!-- not found -->Teofilo Calcagnini (1441–88) of Ferrara</persName>, courtier of Borso d'Este, for which <persName key="person_100215915" role="art">Taddeo Crivelli (fl. 1452–76)</persName> was paid in 1467.</provenance>
                  <provenance>A three-line inscription at the end of the text has been erased.</provenance>
                  <provenance>The Franciscan monastery of <orgName key="org_9" role="fmo"><!-- not found -->Santo Spirito in Reggio Emilia</orgName>, with their ex libris inscriptions (17th cent.): 'Di. S. Spirito di Reggio' (fols. 1r, 89r).</provenance>
                  <provenance>Probably acquired by <persName key="person_17500732" role="fmo">Thomas Coke, Earl of Leicester</persName> in Italy between 1714 and 1717; signed by '<persName key="person_8145335" role="fmo">Thos. Willm. Coke (1754–1842)</persName>; formerly Norfolk, <orgName key="org_8">Holkham Hall</orgName>, MS. 531.</provenance>
                  <provenance> Acquired by the Bodleian in 1981</provenance>
               </history>
